# Environment Configuration Template

## Development
```
APP_ENV=development
APP_DEBUG=true
DB_HOST=localhost
DB_USER=root
DB_PASSWORD=
DB_NAME=school_website_dev
```

## Staging
```
APP_ENV=staging
APP_DEBUG=false
DB_HOST=staging-db.example.com
DB_USER=school_user
DB_PASSWORD=secure_password
DB_NAME=school_website_staging
MAIL_HOST=smtp.example.com
MAIL_PORT=587
MAIL_USER=noreply@school.com
MAIL_PASSWORD=email_password
```

## Production
```
APP_ENV=production
APP_DEBUG=false
DB_HOST=prod-db.example.com
DB_USER=school_user
DB_PASSWORD=very_secure_password
DB_NAME=school_website
MAIL_HOST=smtp.example.com
MAIL_PORT=587
MAIL_USER=noreply@school.com
MAIL_PASSWORD=email_password
LOG_LEVEL=error
```

## How to Use

1. Create `.env` file in project root (don't commit to Git)
2. Copy appropriate values from sections above
3. Update with your actual credentials
4. Never share `.env` file
5. Store sensitive values in GitHub Secrets instead
